results.name: Highly composite deficient numbers: deficient numbers n such that their number of divisors d(n) > d(m) for all deficient numbers m < n.
mathematica: a={}; dm=0; Do[ If[DivisorSigma[1,n]>=2n, Continue[]]; d=DivisorSigma[0,n]; If[d>dm, dm=d; AppendTo[a,n]], {n,1,1000000}]; a
program: (PARI) lista(nn) = {my(maxd = 0); for (n=1, nn, if ((sigma(n) < 2*n) && (numdiv(n) > maxd), maxd = numdiv(n); print1(n, ", ");););} \\ _Michel Marcus_, Apr 17 2018
